  "title": "A blueprint for sustainable, equitable, and planned Urbanisation in India",
  "description": "<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Description:&nbsp;</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">India’s cities are burgeoning. Our cities are&nbsp;expected to host over 800 million citizens by 2050, over half of India’s population.&nbsp;India’s growth story is playing out in our cities, contributing about two-thirds of India’s GDP, and about 70 percent of future employment. There is a clear need to study existing data on spatial contiguity, urban sprawl, migration, jobs, and livelihoods, environment (both built and natural), health (mapping causes and effects of unplanned cities to health outcomes), and synthesise insights to facilitate the creation of a blueprint for sustainable, equitable, and planned urbanisation.</span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;</strong></p><p><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The study aims to study the effect of the natural growth of population in Indian cities and migration happening between rural and urban regions over time. In addition, it will look at various economic and ecological drivers that impact population health outcomes. The analysis will feed into a blueprint for sustainable, equitable, and planned urbanisation that could be replicated in other geographies.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Skill sets:</strong></p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Well-versed with data cleaning, sorting, and reporting tools like Excel, Tableau, SQL, etc</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Advanced statistical analysis</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Data visualization</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Proficiency with R, Python, or any other statistical programming languages</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Applying GIS tools and working with a variety of climate, health, and socioeconomic datasets</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Research acumen</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Writing and communication skills</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Traits expectation:&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Strong analytical and problem-solving skills&nbsp;</strong></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Good verbal, written, and presentation skills</strong></li></ul><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Expected learning:</strong></p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Immersive opportunity to apply data science to real-world problem statements in the field of climate change and health</strong></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">A rigorous policy research experience in sustainable urban planning</strong></li></ul><p><br></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Specific courses required for project execution:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Any advanced statistics/data science course</strong></li></ul><p><br></p>",
